-- NB: we use the builtin function `_<·µá_` here so that the function

+-assoc : Associative _+_

+-identity ≥ zero    = refl

+-comm : Commutative _+_

+-comm (suc m) n = begin-equality
  suc m + n   ‚â°‚ü®‚ü©
  suc (m + n) ‚â°‚ü® cong suc (+-comm m n) ‚ü©
  suc (n + m) ‚â°‚ü® sym (+-suc n m) ‚ü©
  n + suc m   ‚àé

-- It's possible to decide existential and universal predicates up to
-- a limit.
 
module _ {p} {P : Pred ‚Ñï p} (P? : U.Decidable P) where
 
  anyUpTo? : ‚àÄ v ‚Üí Dec (‚àÉ Œª n ‚Üí n < v √ó P n)
  anyUpTo? zero    = no Œª {(_ , () , _)}
  anyUpTo? (suc v) with P? v | anyUpTo? v
  ... | yes Pv | _                  = yes (v , ‚â§-refl , Pv)
  ... | _      | yes (n , n<v , Pn) = yes (n , m‚â§n‚áím‚â§1+n n<v , Pn)
  ... | no ¬¨Pv | no ¬¨Pn<v           = no ¬¨Pn<1+v

    ¬¨Pn<1+v : ¬¨ (‚àÉ Œª n ‚Üí n < suc v √ó P n)
    ¬¨Pn<1+v (n , s‚â§s n‚â§v , Pn) with n ‚âü v

    ... | no  n‚â¢v  = ¬¨Pn<v (n , ‚â§‚àß‚â¢‚áí< n‚â§v n‚â¢v , Pn)
 
  allUpTo? : ‚àÄ v ‚Üí Dec (‚àÄ {n} ‚Üí n < v ‚Üí P n)
  allUpTo? zero    = yes Œª()

  ... | no ¬¨Pv | _        = no Œª prf ‚Üí ¬¨Pv   (prf ‚â§-refl)
  ... | _      | no ¬¨Pn<v = no Œª prf ‚Üí ¬¨Pn<v (prf ‚àò m‚â§n‚áím‚â§1+n)
  ... | yes Pn | yes Pn<v = yes Pn<1+v

      Pn<1+v {n} (s‚â§s n‚â§v) with n ‚âü v
